	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Eleven people were killed when a bus travelling from Zambia crashed in Polokwane on Monday morning. "Eleven people are confirmed to be deceased," said Limpopo Department of Transport spokesperson Matome Moremi. Moremi said eight women and three men were among the deceased. More details to follow.   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  